the is by far the weakest grisham novel i 've ever read . the first two hundred pages creep along at a glacial pace as the protagonist ( joel backman ; more about him later ) wanders italy for nearly 200 pages , learning to speak the language and spending way too much time sipping espresso in quaint trattorias with italian carictatures that would make chico marx cringe . when grisham finally rachets up the action and suspense , it 's all for naught , as the story eventually limps and staggers to a completely listless and anticlimactic ending . as for joel backman , i ca n't think of a more unlikeable and unsympathetic protagonist in recent memory . a disgraced lawyer , lobbyist and traitor that plowed through life in a meaningless quest for wealth and power , all the while causing numerous deaths , and alienating numerous wives and children is supposed to be someone we care about ? does this character redeem himself in any meaningful fashion ? you read the book and decide. .
